;    
;    PURPOSE:  This function returns the full title of an  open  text
;       file.  That  is, the name includes such information as device
;       and actual directory.  It is useful in determining  the  file
;       found  when  there  is directory searching in effect, or when
;       defaults may apply.
;    
;    USAGE:
;    
;       external function PATHNAME (var F: text): FILE_ID;
;    
;    INPUT:
;    
;       F           is the file whose pathname is to be determined.
;    
;    OUTPUT:
;    
;       PATHNAME    is the full title of the file in string format.
;    
;    INCLUDE FILES REQUIRED:
;    
;       CMDUTL.TYP
;       FILUTL.INC
;    
;    ----------------------------------------------------------------
